race.comment: GUS AND GLORY (2) jumped favourite and was too quick with an all-the-way win last start (18.54) at this track in a Maiden over 320m. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Great chance again. URBAN VIVI (4) proved too good on debut over 320m at this track to score by 2.75 lengths (18.31). Harder here but expected to measure up. ZIPPING FLORIDA (7) eye-catching debut run after settling well back but winding up strongly into the frame when second (18.51) at this track over 320m. This looks easier and expected to improve further. DISTORTION (1) placed here at this trip last start - cannot be ignored.
